rComments: Amazing
you won't regret taking any of his classes, really great prof
Best professor ever!
Best professor ever.

Great prof. He is very nice and caring. There is group work in the class (if you approach him with a problem he will help you). He uploads 40 quizzes with 10 questions each (not graded). But they WILL help you for the midterm and final.

I wasn't thrilled about the course because he makes a group project worth a lot and everyone gets the same mark no matter how much or little they do. But, the overall course isn't hard to get an A+. Do the quizzes, study them fully, attend class, take notes and you're guaranteed an A.  DOESN'T POST SLIDES ONLINE. GO TO CLASS.

He makes his expectations straight forward, just show up to class, pay attention, do the quizzes he posts online and you won't need to buy the textbook. He isn't a hard marker for the group projects, just prove to him that you learned something in his class.

He is by far one of my favourite professors at Uottawa! He is very passionate about what he does and makes his lectures very interesting and interactive. we learn from him as much as he learns from us. he is very funny and wants his students to succeed. he provides us with online quizzes to practice course material uses them in his midterm/exams.

He seems to really care about his students but he can also be rude.. A midterm, group project paper and presentation(not every member has to present), and a final test. I would recommend not buying his textbook because he gives you practice quizes that are exact wording. He tells you  what from class is on the midterm and final. Easy A+

Do the online tests, remember them, and you'll pass quite easily. It's actually quite easy to get an A. Just don't lag on joining a group for the group presentations as it might become a problem for you later on in the semester. Highly recommend this prof. Also you don't need the textbook unless you want an A+

Eid's classes are by far the best I've had yet at Uottawa! I was in CMN 3105 & 4100 and loved both. He guarantees his students at least an 80% grade in his class if they put in the effort. He has practices quizzes for each of his exams and draws 80% of the questions on his exams from the practices quizzes! TAKE HIS CLASSES. You won't regret it!
Tells you when to write things down, otherwise you don't need to. Posted online quizzes to prepare for (all multiple choice) exams. Gave bonus points for in-class participation. Super clear.

Dr. Eid, by far, one of the best human being and the best professors I got taught by. He is amazing. His exams are easy. Also, he is very helpful inside and outside the class. If you have any questions, he is there for you. I wish him the best!

Such an amazing prof, I would take another class with him again. He has a lot of knowledge in his field and his classes are very interesting. The exams are extremely easy. Professor Eid genuinely wants his students to do well.
I will take a class with him again, anytime! Like his style of teaching. Do your readings and you're good!

Dr. Eid is an excellent professor at the University of Ottawa. His Media Ethics class is interesting and informative; perhaps one of the best courses I have taken. He organizes the course so as to allow students to do well as long as you do the quizzes and make an effort. Overall Dr. Eid is a really interesting teacher that I would highly recommend

Bien que j'ai suivi le cours en anglais, j'ai recu de bonnes appréciations et des encouragements de la part de Dr . Eid. Il se soucie vraiment de ses élèves et de leur succès. C'est l'un des meilleurs professeurs que je ai eus. Sans hésitation, je vous le recommande.
Great prof. If you pay attention and do the quizes you will pass, and do well.

if you are not good at math or numbers, take quantitative with Eid! he makes it very easy. great prof that really makes it possible for everyone to get an A (as long as they put in a bit of effort of course)..memorize the online quizzes are you'll do great!

great prof. really wants all his students to suceed, he told the class if they get a A- they should drop it & take him again haha DO THE ONLINE QUIZZES and you'll get an A guarunteed! don't buy the textbook, it's a good read but it's expensive and not even used, all the important notes are in his slides. the best way to take quantitative methods!!!

Great teacher who goes the extra mile to help his students. He even remembers his students and often greets us when walking by. I would recommend him to any student. I cannot forget to talk about how brilliant he is at what he teaches and even if you ask an unclear question he will have understood it and respond clearly and concisely.

Great teacher, makes it really easy for students to succeed on their own. His group policies are weird though - if a person disagrees with their group evaluation, they can dispute it, despite it representing the majority of the members. I fail to see the point of a challengable peer evaluation. Overall really nice though!
Eid is a very smart teacher and really knows his stuff! Also, he wants all his students to do well...!

Dr. Mahmoud Eid is by far one of the best professors I have had since starting at Ottawa U. He really cares about his students and their sucess in his courses. He will go out of his way to help students out, and is quick to reply to e-mails. I would HIGHLY recommend him as a professor and wouldn't hesitate taking another one of his classes again!!
This guy is great! His practice quizzes make up 80% of his exam, and he was very clear about what he wanted. He was really kind and funny too.

Great prof. He uses the virtual campus religiously and makes practice tests for students on the web ct. He told us exactly what would be on the exam, and really wants students to succeed. Very practical teacher.

Textbook was rarely used, but really helpful for the final essay.  Showing up was pretty much optional.  He's really helpful if you go to his office.  He loves class participation and gives bonus marks for participation in class discussions.

Pretty good professor. Very helpful, although coarse material is a little dry. Gives good marks. Class could be more interesting. Textbook was not absolutely neccesary although provided insight into coarse material.
Ok prof... i guess. very very unclear when answering questions. Ethics is a boring boring class.
